    "With the recent advances in generative AI, such as transformer-based architectures, large language models (LLMs), and diffusion models, we have witnessed the development of high-performance generative methodologies in molecular [40] [41] [42] [43] and crystal generation [44] [45] [46].",
    "These methods generally include material symmetry such as invariance, equivalence, and periodicity 40, 41, 44 into the model architecture to better predict the 3D conformations of material systems.",
    "However, to the best of our knowledge, there are few studies that leverage advanced generative AI techniques for polymer generation.",
    "This presents significant opportunities to develop more effective solutions to the challenges in this field.",
    "Given that the polymer electrolytes of our interest in this study are generally amorphous materials with high structural stochasticity, we here mainly focus on the 2D representation of polymers during the generative task."
